					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10297313#post-4152413</guid>
				<title>Author post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10297313/nine-tales-from-the-cativerse#post-4152413</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 13 Feb 2019 18:06:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MathBrush</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2026461</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hello! This is an alternate version of the Foundation where everyone and everything is cats.</p> <p>This tale includes 4 images of cat-versions of SCPs, as well as micro-tales involving 5 cat SCPs.</p> <p>I hope you all enjoy!</p> <p>All 4 images are taken from Wikimedia commons, as public domain images:</p> <p><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Cat_Vessel_MET_1978.412.89_b.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Cat_Vessel_MET_1978.412.89_b.jpg</a></p> <p><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Moggessa_di_Qu%C3%A1_mummified_cat_2008_1004_04.JPG">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Moggessa_di_Qu%C3%A1_mummified_cat_2008_1004_04.JPG</a></p> <p><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flickr_-_Nic%27s_events_-_London_-_14-15_Dec_2007_-_018.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flickr_-_Nic%27s_events_-_London_-_14-15_Dec_2007_-_018.jpg</a></p> <p><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The-cat.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:The-cat.jpg</a></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
